Note:
RED-BLACK TREE - Self-Balancing Binary Search Tree Tier 0 Primitive

This file implements a left-leaning-allowed red-black tree with O(log n)
insert, delete, search, min, max, successor, predecessor.

Invariants (Cormen / classic Red-Black):
1) Every node is RED (0) or BLACK (1).
2) The root is BLACK.
3) Every leaf (NIL sentinel) is BLACK.
4) If a node is RED, both children are BLACK.
5) For every node, all paths from it to descendant NILs contain the same
   number of BLACK nodes ("black height").

Node structure (56 bytes):
  offset 0:  key (8 bytes)
  offset 8:  value (8 bytes)
  offset 16: left child pointer (8 bytes)
  offset 24: right child pointer (8 bytes)
  offset 32: parent pointer (8 bytes)
  offset 40: color (8 bytes; 0 = RED, 1 = BLACK)
  offset 48: padding to 56 (preserves 8-byte slot alignment)

Tree structure (24 bytes):
  offset 0:  root pointer (NIL sentinel if empty)
  offset 8:  size
  offset 16: nil sentinel pointer (single shared BLACK NIL node)
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Let RB_NODE_SIZE be 56
Let RB_HEADER_SIZE be 24
Let RB_KEY_OFFSET be 0
Let RB_VALUE_OFFSET be 8
Let RB_LEFT_OFFSET be 16
Let RB_RIGHT_OFFSET be 24
Let RB_PARENT_OFFSET be 32
Let RB_COLOR_OFFSET be 40
Let RB_COLOR_RED be 0
Let RB_COLOR_BLACK be 1

Note: ============================================================================
Note: NODE PRIMITIVES
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate a new RB node with key/value/parent/children set as supplied
and color RED. All inserts start as RED so we never violate the
"equal black height" invariant on insertion; the fix-up loop then
restores the no-two-reds-in-a-row invariant.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
56-byte allocation, fields set per layout, color = RED.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: 56 bytes per node.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rb_node_create" takes key as Integer, value as Integer, nil_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node be proc allocate from Layout with RB_NODE_SIZE
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, RB_KEY_OFFSET, key
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, RB_VALUE_OFFSET, value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, RB_LEFT_OFFSET, nil_node
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET, nil_node
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, RB_PARENT_OFFSET, nil_node
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_RED
    Return node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TREE CONSTRUCTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Create an empty tree. Allocates a single NIL sentinel that all leaf
pointers and the root-of-empty-tree share, simplifying the fix-up
loops by removing a null-check at every recursion step.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Allocate header (24 bytes).
2) Allocate nil sentinel (56 bytes), color = BLACK, key/value = 0,
   children/parent pointing back at itself (cycle by design - that
   makes the fix-up loops safe even if they walk through the NIL).
3) Set tree.root = nil, size = 0, tree.nil = nil.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: 80 bytes (header + NIL).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure of either piece.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rb_tree_create" returns Integer:
    Let tree be proc allocate from Layout with RB_HEADER_SIZE
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nil_node be proc allocate from Layout with RB_NODE_SIZE
    If nil_node is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with tree
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with nil_node, RB_KEY_OFFSET, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with nil_node, RB_VALUE_OFFSET, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with nil_node, RB_LEFT_OFFSET, nil_node
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with nil_node, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET, nil_node
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with nil_node, RB_PARENT_OFFSET, nil_node
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with nil_node, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_BLACK
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 0, nil_node
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 16, nil_node
    Return tree
End Process

@Reasoning
Free all real nodes plus the NIL sentinel and the header.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Iterative postorder via a hand-rolled work stack of node pointers
allocated as a flat dynamic array. We use a fixed initial capacity of
64 entries and grow geometrically; this avoids depending on the Stack
primitive in case that module is being audited concurrently.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(h).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller-owned.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rb_tree_destroy" takes tree as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nil_node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 16
    Let root be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    Let cap be 64
    Let buf_bytes be cap multiplied by 8
    Let buf be proc allocate from Layout with buf_bytes
    If buf is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with nil_node
        proc deallocate from Layout with tree
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sp be 0
    If root is not equal to nil_node:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with buf, 0, root
        Set sp to 1
    End If
    While sp is greater than 0:
        Set sp to sp minus 1
        Let off be sp multiplied by 8
        Let node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with buf, off
        Let left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
        Let right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET
        Let need be sp plus 2
        If need is greater than cap:
            Let new_cap be cap multiplied by 2
            Let new_bytes be new_cap multiplied by 8
            Let new_buf be proc allocate from Layout with new_bytes
            If new_buf is equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with buf
                proc deallocate from Layout with nil_node
                proc deallocate from Layout with tree
                Return 0
            End If
            Let copy_bytes be cap multiplied by 8
            proc memory_copy from Memory with new_buf, buf, copy_bytes
            proc deallocate from Layout with buf
            Set buf to new_buf
            Set cap to new_cap
        End If
        If left is not equal to nil_node:
            Let l_off be sp multiplied by 8
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with buf, l_off, left
            Set sp to sp plus 1
        End If
        If right is not equal to nil_node:
            Let r_off be sp multiplied by 8
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with buf, r_off, right
            Set sp to sp plus 1
        End If
        proc deallocate from Layout with node
    End While
    proc deallocate from Layout with buf
    proc deallocate from Layout with nil_node
    proc deallocate from Layout with tree
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Element count.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Read size field.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rb_tree_size" takes tree as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 8
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ROTATIONS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Left-rotate around node x: x's right child y takes x's position; x
becomes y's left child; y's old left subtree becomes x's new right
subtree. Used in the insertion and deletion fix-up loops to rebalance.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
y = x.right
x.right = y.left
if y.left != nil: y.left.parent = x
y.parent = x.parent
if x.parent == nil: tree.root = y
elif x == x.parent.left: x.parent.left = y
else: x.parent.right = y
y.left = x
x.parent = y
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper. Caller guarantees x has a non-nil right child.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rb_left_rotate" takes tree as Integer, x as Integer returns Integer:
    Let nil_node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 16
    Let y be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with x, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET
    Let y_left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with y, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with x, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET, y_left
    If y_left is not equal to nil_node:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with y_left, RB_PARENT_OFFSET, x
    End If
    Let x_parent be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with x, RB_PARENT_OFFSET
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with y, RB_PARENT_OFFSET, x_parent
    If x_parent is equal to nil_node:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 0, y
    Otherwise:
        Let xp_left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with x_parent, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
        If x is equal to xp_left:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with x_parent, RB_LEFT_OFFSET, y
        Otherwise:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with x_parent, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET, y
        End If
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with y, RB_LEFT_OFFSET, x
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with x, RB_PARENT_OFFSET, y
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Right-rotate around node y: y's left child x takes y's position; y
becomes x's right child; x's old right subtree becomes y's new left
subtree. Mirror of left-rotate.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Mirror of rb_left_rotate.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper. Caller guarantees y has a non-nil left child.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rb_right_rotate" takes tree as Integer, y as Integer returns Integer:
    Let nil_node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 16
    Let x be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with y, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
    Let x_right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with x, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with y, RB_LEFT_OFFSET, x_right
    If x_right is not equal to nil_node:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with x_right, RB_PARENT_OFFSET, y
    End If
    Let y_parent be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with y, RB_PARENT_OFFSET
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with x, RB_PARENT_OFFSET, y_parent
    If y_parent is equal to nil_node:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 0, x
    Otherwise:
        Let yp_right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with y_parent, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET
        If y is equal to yp_right:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with y_parent, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET, x
        Otherwise:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with y_parent, RB_LEFT_OFFSET, x
        End If
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with x, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET, y
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with y, RB_PARENT_OFFSET, x
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: INSERT + FIXUP
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Insertion fixup: walk up from the newly-inserted RED node z restoring
the no-two-reds invariant. The case analysis follows the standard
"uncle-color" CLRS dichotomy:
- If uncle is RED: recolor (parent and uncle BLACK, grandparent RED),
  then move z to grandparent and continue.
- If uncle is BLACK and z is the "inner" child (zigzag): rotate to
  straighten.
- If uncle is BLACK and z is the "outer" child (zigzag): recolor and
  rotate around grandparent to push the violation away.
The loop terminates when the parent is BLACK or z becomes the root.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Iterative left/right mirror cases. Final step paints the root BLACK.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(log n) amortized; the worst-case full walk is bounded by the
tree height which is O(log n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rb_insert_fixup" takes tree as Integer, z as Integer returns Integer:
    Let nil_node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 16
    Let z_parent be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with z, RB_PARENT_OFFSET
    Let parent_color be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with z_parent, RB_COLOR_OFFSET
    While parent_color is equal to RB_COLOR_RED:
        Let zp be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with z, RB_PARENT_OFFSET
        Let zpp be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with zp, RB_PARENT_OFFSET
        Let zpp_left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with zpp, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
        If zp is equal to zpp_left:
            Let uncle be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with zpp, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET
            Let uncle_color be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with uncle, RB_COLOR_OFFSET
            If uncle_color is equal to RB_COLOR_RED:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with zp, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_BLACK
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with uncle, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_BLACK
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with zpp, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_RED
                Set z to zpp
            Otherwise:
                Let zp_right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with zp, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET
                If z is equal to zp_right:
                    Set z to zp
                    proc rb_left_rotate with tree, z
                End If
                Let new_zp be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with z, RB_PARENT_OFFSET
                Let new_zpp be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with new_zp, RB_PARENT_OFFSET
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with new_zp, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_BLACK
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with new_zpp, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_RED
                proc rb_right_rotate with tree, new_zpp
            End If
        Otherwise:
            Let uncle be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with zpp, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
            Let uncle_color be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with uncle, RB_COLOR_OFFSET
            If uncle_color is equal to RB_COLOR_RED:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with zp, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_BLACK
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with uncle, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_BLACK
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with zpp, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_RED
                Set z to zpp
            Otherwise:
                Let zp_left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with zp, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
                If z is equal to zp_left:
                    Set z to zp
                    proc rb_right_rotate with tree, z
                End If
                Let new_zp be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with z, RB_PARENT_OFFSET
                Let new_zpp be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with new_zp, RB_PARENT_OFFSET
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with new_zp, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_BLACK
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with new_zpp, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_RED
                proc rb_left_rotate with tree, new_zpp
            End If
        End If
        Let new_z_parent be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with z, RB_PARENT_OFFSET
        Set parent_color to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with new_z_parent, RB_COLOR_OFFSET
    End While
    Let root be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with root, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_BLACK
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Public insert: find the right BST position, link in a new RED node,
then run the fixup. Duplicate keys are allowed; equal keys descend
left as a stable tiebreak.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Standard BST descent with nil-sentinel checks; allocate node when the
chosen child slot is nil; call fixup.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(log n). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rb_tree_insert" takes tree as Integer, key as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nil_node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 16
    Let z be proc rb_node_create with key, value, nil_node
    If z is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let y be nil_node
    Let x be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    While x is not equal to nil_node:
        Set y to x
        Let x_key be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with x, RB_KEY_OFFSET
        If key is less than or equal to x_key:
            Set x to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with x, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
        Otherwise:
            Set x to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with x, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET
        End If
    End While
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with z, RB_PARENT_OFFSET, y
    If y is equal to nil_node:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 0, z
    Otherwise:
        Let y_key be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with y, RB_KEY_OFFSET
        If key is less than or equal to y_key:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with y, RB_LEFT_OFFSET, z
        Otherwise:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with y, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET, z
        End If
    End If
    proc rb_insert_fixup with tree, z
    Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 8, size plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SEARCH / MIN / MAX
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Standard BST search by key. Returns the value, or 0 if not found.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk from root through left/right based on key comparison; nil exit
returns 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(log n). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rb_tree_search" takes tree as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nil_node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 16
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    While cur is not equal to nil_node:
        Let cv be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, RB_KEY_OFFSET
        If key is equal to cv:
            Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, RB_VALUE_OFFSET
        End If
        If key is less than cv:
            Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
        Otherwise:
            Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET
        End If
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Containment predicate distinct from search to disambiguate "found but
value is 0" from "absent". Returns 1 if present, 0 otherwise.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Same descent as search but returns 1 on the match branch instead of
the value field.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(log n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rb_tree_contains" takes tree as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nil_node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 16
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    While cur is not equal to nil_node:
        Let cv be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, RB_KEY_OFFSET
        If key is equal to cv:
            Return 1
        End If
        If key is less than cv:
            Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
        Otherwise:
            Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET
        End If
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Minimum and maximum key lookups walk left or right from root.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk through left children to minimum; right children to maximum.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(log n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rb_tree_min" takes tree as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nil_node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 16
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    If cur is equal to nil_node:
        Return 0
    End If
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
        If left is equal to nil_node:
            Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, RB_KEY_OFFSET
        End If
        Set cur to left
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Walk right children for the maximum key.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Mirror of rb_tree_min.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(log n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rb_tree_max" takes tree as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nil_node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 16
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    If cur is equal to nil_node:
        Return 0
    End If
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET
        If right is equal to nil_node:
            Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, RB_KEY_OFFSET
        End If
        Set cur to right
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: DELETE + FIXUP
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
RB transplant helper: replace subtree rooted at u with subtree rooted
at v in the parent's child slot. Required by rb_tree_delete.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) If u.parent == nil, tree.root = v.
2) Else if u == u.parent.left, u.parent.left = v.
3) Else u.parent.right = v.
4) v.parent = u.parent (even if v is nil - the nil sentinel's parent
   slot is used by the deletion fix-up).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rb_transplant" takes tree as Integer, u as Integer, v as Integer returns Integer:
    Let nil_node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 16
    Let u_parent be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with u, RB_PARENT_OFFSET
    If u_parent is equal to nil_node:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 0, v
    Otherwise:
        Let up_left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with u_parent, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
        If u is equal to up_left:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with u_parent, RB_LEFT_OFFSET, v
        Otherwise:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with u_parent, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET, v
        End If
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with v, RB_PARENT_OFFSET, u_parent
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Deletion fix-up: restore the "equal black height" invariant after a
black node was spliced out. The case analysis follows CLRS with the
left/right mirror.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
While x is not the root and x is BLACK:
  Let w = sibling of x.
  Case 1 - sibling RED: recolor and rotate so sibling becomes BLACK.
  Case 2 - sibling BLACK with both children BLACK: paint sibling RED,
           move x up.
  Case 3 - sibling BLACK, near nephew RED, far nephew BLACK: rotate
           sibling, recolor, fall into case 4.
  Case 4 - sibling BLACK, far nephew RED: rotate parent, recolor, x =
           root (terminates loop).
Finally paint x BLACK to absorb any extra black token.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(log n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rb_delete_fixup" takes tree as Integer, x as Integer returns Integer:
    Let nil_node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 16
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let root be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
        If x is equal to root:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with x, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_BLACK
            Return 1
        End If
        Let x_color be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with x, RB_COLOR_OFFSET
        If x_color is not equal to RB_COLOR_BLACK:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with x, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_BLACK
            Return 1
        End If
        Let xp be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with x, RB_PARENT_OFFSET
        Let xp_left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with xp, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
        If x is equal to xp_left:
            Let w be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with xp, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET
            Let w_color be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with w, RB_COLOR_OFFSET
            If w_color is equal to RB_COLOR_RED:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with w, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_BLACK
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with xp, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_RED
                proc rb_left_rotate with tree, xp
                Set w to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with xp, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET
            End If
            Let wl be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with w, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
            Let wr be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with w, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET
            Let wl_color be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with wl, RB_COLOR_OFFSET
            Let wr_color be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with wr, RB_COLOR_OFFSET
            If wl_color is equal to RB_COLOR_BLACK:
                If wr_color is equal to RB_COLOR_BLACK:
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with w, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_RED
                    Set x to xp
                Otherwise:
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with w, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with xp, RB_COLOR_OFFSET
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with xp, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_BLACK
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with wr, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_BLACK
                    proc rb_left_rotate with tree, xp
                    Set x to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
                End If
            Otherwise:
                If wr_color is equal to RB_COLOR_BLACK:
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with wl, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_BLACK
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with w, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_RED
                    proc rb_right_rotate with tree, w
                    Set w to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with xp, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET
                    Set wr to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with w, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET
                End If
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with w, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with xp, RB_COLOR_OFFSET
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with xp, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_BLACK
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with wr, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_BLACK
                proc rb_left_rotate with tree, xp
                Set x to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
            End If
        Otherwise:
            Let w be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with xp, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
            Let w_color be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with w, RB_COLOR_OFFSET
            If w_color is equal to RB_COLOR_RED:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with w, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_BLACK
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with xp, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_RED
                proc rb_right_rotate with tree, xp
                Set w to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with xp, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
            End If
            Let wl be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with w, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
            Let wr be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with w, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET
            Let wl_color be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with wl, RB_COLOR_OFFSET
            Let wr_color be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with wr, RB_COLOR_OFFSET
            If wr_color is equal to RB_COLOR_BLACK:
                If wl_color is equal to RB_COLOR_BLACK:
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with w, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_RED
                    Set x to xp
                Otherwise:
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with w, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with xp, RB_COLOR_OFFSET
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with xp, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_BLACK
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with wl, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_BLACK
                    proc rb_right_rotate with tree, xp
                    Set x to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
                End If
            Otherwise:
                If wl_color is equal to RB_COLOR_BLACK:
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with wr, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_BLACK
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with w, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_RED
                    proc rb_left_rotate with tree, w
                    Set w to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with xp, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
                    Set wl to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with w, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
                End If
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with w, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with xp, RB_COLOR_OFFSET
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with xp, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_BLACK
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with wl, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, RB_COLOR_BLACK
                proc rb_right_rotate with tree, xp
                Set x to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Delete the node with the given key. Standard CLRS: find z, splice out
either z or its in-order successor depending on whether z has two
children. Run fix-up if a BLACK node was removed.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Find z by key. If not found, return 0.
2) Save y_original_color = y.color where y is the node actually
   spliced out (z itself if z has at most one child, otherwise z's
   successor).
3) If z has at most one non-nil child, transplant that child for z.
4) Else: y = subtree-min of z.right. If y's parent is z, just set
   x.parent = y; else transplant y with y.right, attach z.right under y.
   Then transplant z with y, attach z.left under y, copy z.color into y.
5) Free z, decrement size.
6) If y_original_color was BLACK, run rb_delete_fixup on x.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(log n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 if key not found.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rb_tree_delete" takes tree as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nil_node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 16
    Let z be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    While z is not equal to nil_node:
        Let zk be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with z, RB_KEY_OFFSET
        If key is equal to zk:
            Note: found
            Let y be z
            Let y_original_color be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with y, RB_COLOR_OFFSET
            Let x be nil_node
            Let z_left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with z, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
            Let z_right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with z, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET
            If z_left is equal to nil_node:
                Set x to z_right
                proc rb_transplant with tree, z, z_right
            Otherwise:
                If z_right is equal to nil_node:
                    Set x to z_left
                    proc rb_transplant with tree, z, z_left
                Otherwise:
                    Note: y = subtree-min of z.right
                    Let m be z_right
                    While 1 is equal to 1:
                        Let m_left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with m, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
                        If m_left is equal to nil_node:
                            Return 0 plus proc rb_delete_with_successor with tree, z, m, x
                        End If
                        Set m to m_left
                    End While
                End If
            End If
            proc deallocate from Layout with z
            Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 8
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 8, size minus 1
            If y_original_color is equal to RB_COLOR_BLACK:
                proc rb_delete_fixup with tree, x
            End If
            Return 1
        End If
        If key is less than zk:
            Set z to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with z, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
        Otherwise:
            Set z to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with z, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET
        End If
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Inner helper that finishes the two-child deletion case. Split out so
the main rb_tree_delete loop stays under one screen and the deletion
case analysis is locally complete.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
y = successor (passed as 'm'). x = y.right (passed as 'x' but read
fresh because the caller passed nil_node by convention).
y_original_color = y.color.
If y.parent == z: x.parent = y.
Else: transplant y with y.right; y.right = z.right; y.right.parent = y.
Transplant z with y; y.left = z.left; y.left.parent = y; y.color =
z.color. Free z. Decrement size. If y_original_color was BLACK, run
fixup on x.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) given the supplied pointers.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rb_delete_with_successor" takes tree as Integer, z as Integer, y as Integer, x_unused as Integer returns Integer:
    Let nil_node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 16
    Let y_original_color be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with y, RB_COLOR_OFFSET
    Let x be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with y, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET
    Let y_parent be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with y, RB_PARENT_OFFSET
    If y_parent is equal to z:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with x, RB_PARENT_OFFSET, y
    Otherwise:
        proc rb_transplant with tree, y, x
        Let z_right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with z, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with y, RB_RIGHT_OFFSET, z_right
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with z_right, RB_PARENT_OFFSET, y
    End If
    proc rb_transplant with tree, z, y
    Let z_left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with z, RB_LEFT_OFFSET
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with y, RB_LEFT_OFFSET, z_left
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with z_left, RB_PARENT_OFFSET, y
    Let z_color be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with z, RB_COLOR_OFFSET
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with y, RB_COLOR_OFFSET, z_color
    proc deallocate from Layout with z
    Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 8, size minus 1
    If y_original_color is equal to RB_COLOR_BLACK:
        proc rb_delete_fixup with tree, x
    End If
    Return 1
End Process
